16:43
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='992000' id='t-992000'>SS: So we have a bi-species environment, we call it a &quot;panhomoculture.&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='999000' id='t-999000'>We're learning how to become like them.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1001000' id='t-1001000'>We're learning how to communicate with them,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1003000' id='t-1003000'>in really high-pitched tones.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1005000' id='t-1005000'>We're learning that they probably have a language in the wild.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1009000' id='t-1009000'>And they're learning to become like us.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1011000' id='t-1011000'>Because we believe that it's not biology; it's culture.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1014000' id='t-1014000'>So we're sharing tools and technology and language</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='1018000' id='t-1018000'>with another species.</span>
</span>
</p>
